        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Wood refers to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_2626.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Rudolf Albert von Kölliker</ref> and Kölliker 1869–72. No letter from CD to Wood on this subject has been found, but see the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7674.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Wood, 11 April 1871</ref>, and <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 18, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7230.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to R. A. von Kölliker, 14 June 1870</ref> and nn. 1 and 3.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD describes this experiment in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref>, pp. 297–8.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">CD discusses the erection of hairs, feathers, and spines in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref>, pp. 95–104.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f4">See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-7674.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from John Wood, 11 April 1871</ref> and n. 1.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f5">CD compares the occipito-frontalis of humans to the panniculus carnosus of animals in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref>, p. 298.</note>
        </div>        
            
